{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775832576577,"sessionID":"ses_28823720fffeDGdaCyHttqNdro","part":{"id":"prt_d77dce22f001eU7NFRYHElHBYD","messageID":"msg_d77dcd6c7001mXeGVDLtYHR09A","sessionID":"ses_28823720fffeDGdaCyHttqNdro","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_4522e558aa29487a919b0f3d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find filled proposal examples","prompt":"Search through the proposals in /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-001/ through AR-009/ to find any that have actual content (not just TODO placeholders). Read 2-3 that are filled in and return their full content. Also check the pkg/store directory structure at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/ to see what files exist there. Return all findings.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288231029ffei7RpkURUmi1wgl (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a complete summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## Proposals AR-001 through AR-009: Content Status\n\nOut of the 9 proposals examined (AR-001 through AR-009), **8 are fully filled in with substantive content**, and **1 is a TODO placeholder**:\n\n| Proposal | Status | Topic |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| AR-001 | **FILLED** (105 lines) | CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition |\n| AR-002 | **FILLED** (128 lines) | CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition |\n| AR-003 | **FILLED** (116 lines) | CRD Shared Types and Constants |\n| AR-004 | **FILLED** (185 lines) | WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework |\n| AR-005 | **FILLED** (139 lines) | Sandbox Creation Handler |\n| AR-006 | **FILLED** (129 lines) | Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management |\n| AR-007 | **FILLED** (127 lines) | K8s Reconciler Controller |\n| AR-008 | **FILLED** (145 lines) | Sandbox GC Scheduled Cleanup |\n| AR-009 | **TODO PLACEHOLDER** (54 lines) | Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core |\n\nAR-009 is the only TODO placeholder. Its `proposal.md` has metadata filled in but every section body contains only `<!-- TODO: ... -->` comments.\n\n---\n\n## Full Content of 3 Representative Filled Proposals\n\nI read all three files (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md) for AR-001, AR-004, and AR-007. Here are the key details:\n\n### AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n- **Files**: `proposal.md` (105 lines), `design.md` (636 lines), `tasks.md` (199 lines)\n- **Module**: `pkg/apis`\n- **Language**: Go, Size: S\n- **Purpose**: Defines the `AgentRuntime` CRD Go types under `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`, including `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `AgentRuntimeList`, and `SandboxTemplate` (which embeds `corev1.PodSpec`). Registers GroupVersion `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n- **Key design decisions**: Embeds `corev1.PodSpec` directly rather than a custom subset; uses kubebuilder markers for validation (`+kubebuilder:validation:Required`, `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`); generates DeepCopy via `controller-gen object`.\n- **Tasks**: 14 task groups (T-001 through T-014), covering directory creation, doc.go, groupversion_info.go, register.go, shared types, core type definition, Scheme registration, DeepCopy generation, and comprehensive unit tests (Scheme registration, GVK/GVR constants, defaults, DeepCopy, ProtocolType enum).\n\n### AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n- **Files**: `proposal.md` (185 lines), `design.md` (636 lines), `tasks.md` (255 lines), plus `delta-spec.md`\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go, Size: M\n- **Purpose**: Establishes a Gin-based HTTP service framework for WorkloadManager, exposing RESTful CRUD endpoints for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, plus health/readiness probes.\n- **Key design decisions**: Uses Gin (consistent with Router component); read/write separation (GET via Informer Lister, POST/PUT/DELETE via Typed Client); unified JSON error response format with request ID tracking; graceful shutdown via `http.Server.Shutdown()`.\n- **Routes**: `GET /healthz`, `GET /readyz`, `POST/GET/PUT/DELETE /api/v1/agentruntimes`, `POST/GET/PUT/DELETE /api/v1/codeinterpreters`.\n- **Tasks**: 17 task groups (T-001 through T-017), covering Gin dependency, response helpers, config management, health handlers, CRUD handlers for both resource types, request ID middleware, route registration, server lifecycle, and full validation gates (80% coverage, T/C > 0.4).\n\n### AR-007: K8s Reconciler Controller\n- **Files**: `proposal.md` (127 lines), `design.md` (549 lines), `tasks.md` (399 lines), plus `delta-spec.md`\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go, Size: L\n- **Purpose**: Implements a `SandboxReconciler` using the standard Informer + Workqueue pattern to continuously watch AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CR changes and reconcile them with Store (Redis/Valkey) session state.\n- **Key design decisions**: Uses `SharedInformerFactory` for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and Pod informers; `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` with exponential backoff (5s initial, 5min max, 15 retries); state mapping from K8s Conditions to Store status (pending/running/terminated); Prometheus metrics exposure; graceful shutdown with `ShutDownWithDrain()` and 30s timeout.\n- **Architecture**: Event callbacks enqueue keys -> worker goroutines dequeue and call `syncHandler` -> syncHandler tries AR lister, then CI lister, then Pod fallback -> executes type-specific reconcile logic -> updates Store.\n- **Tasks**: 25 task groups (T-001 through T-025), covering internal types, metrics, reconciler struct/constructor, event handlers, state mapping, per-resource reconcile logic (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod), sync/worker loop, Run/graceful shutdown, handler integration, E2E tests, and full validation gates.\n\n---\n\n## pkg/store Directory Structure\n\nThe `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/` directory contains **5 files**:\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `store.go` | 35 | Defines the `Store` interface (10 methods: StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, GetSandbox, ListSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, Ping, Close) and the `Storage()` singleton accessor |\n| `store_redis.go` | 235 | Full Redis implementation of the Store interface using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`; includes sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking |\n| `store_valkey.go` | 246 | Full Valkey implementation of the Store interface using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`; mirrors the Redis implementation with Valkey-specific client API |\n| `singleton.go` | 31 | `initStore()` function using `sync.Once` to lazily initialize the store; reads `STORE_TYPE` env var (defaults to \"redis\") and instantiates either Redis or Valkey |\n| `codec.go` | 19 | JSON encode/decode helpers (`encodeSandboxInfo`, `decodeSandboxInfo`) for serializing `types.SandboxInfo` to/from byte slices |\n\nAll 5 files are fully implemented Go source code with no TODO placeholders. The store layer provides a clean abstraction with two interchangeable backends (Redis and Valkey) behind a common `Store` interface.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288231029ffei7RpkURUmi1wgl","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find filled proposal examples","time":{"start":1775832461268,"end":1775832576575}}}}
